        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>returns a vector with unique integer values, each representing a dimension of the box; the dimensions are sorted according to the sizes of the box along each dimension: the dimension with the smallest size is first, largest size - last. E.g. findSortedBoxDims( Box3f( {0, 0, 0}, {2, 1, 3} ) ) == Vector3i(1, 0, 2) </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para>bubble sort (optimal for small array)</para>
        </inbodydescription>
